    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<h1>UZ (Person)</h1><p>1. Aram’s firstborn son and a descendant of Shem (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen10:23\">Gn 10:23</a>). In the parallel passage in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr1:17\">1&nbsp;Chronicles 1:17</a>, Uz is linked directly to Shem without mention of Aram. He is perhaps the forefather of the Aramean nation situated in the Syrian desert regions.</p><p>2. Firstborn son of Abraham’s brother Nahor by his concubine, Milcah (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:21\">Gn 22:21</a>).</p><p>3. Son of Dishan and the grandson of Seir the Horite (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen36:28\">Gn 36:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr1:42\">1&nbsp;Chr 1:42</a>).</p>",
